{
  "Work and Energy Applications": "工作与能源应用",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "A force F(x) = 6x^2 N moves an object from x = 0 to x = 3 meters. What is the work done?": "F(x)力 = 6x=2N 将物体从 x = 0 移动到 x = 3米。 完成了什么工作?",
  "W = integral from 0 to 3 of 6x^2 dx = 6[x^3/3] from 0 to 3 = 2(27) = 54 J.": "W = 6x2 dx 0到 3 等于 6[x3]/3,0 = 3 = 2(27) = 54 J = 6x2 dx 0 到 3 = 6[x3] = 6[x3/3],0 = 3 = 2(27) = 54 J = 6x2 dx = 6[x3] = 6[x3] = 6[x3] = 3 = 3 = 5 = = 5 J = = 6x2 = = = 6x2 = = 6x2 dx2 dx 0 到 = = 6[x3] = = = 6[x3] = = = 6[x3] = = = = = 6x2 = = = = 6 [x3 = = = = = 6 [x2 = = = = = = = = 0 = = = = = = = 0 = = = = = = = = = = = = = 6= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = 0 = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = 0 = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =",
  "A spring has a natural length of 20 cm. It takes 12 J of work to stretch it to 26 cm. What is the spring constant?": "泉水的自然长度为20厘米。 春天的常数是多少?",
  "The stretch is 0.06 m. Work = (1/2)k*x^2, so 12 = (1/2)k(0.06)^2 = (1/2)k(0.0036). Therefore k = 24/0.0036 = 6667 N/m (approximately).": "伸展面积为0.06米。工作=(1/2)k*x__2,所以12=(1/2)k(0.06)__2 =(1/2)k(0.0036),因此k = 24/0.0036 = 6667 N/m(约合)。",
  "If the work required to stretch a spring 0.2 m from natural length is 4 J, what is the spring constant k?": "如果从自然长度延伸0.2米处的春季工作需要4J,那么春季常数K是什么?",
  "W = (1/2)kx^2, so 4 = (1/2)k(0.2)^2 = (1/2)k(0.04) = 0.02k. Therefore k = 4/0.02 = 200 N/m.": "W = (1/2)kx__2, 所以 4 = (1/2)k (0. 2)2 = (1/2)k (0.04) = 0.02k。 因此 k = 4/0.02 = 200 N/m。",
  "What is the elastic potential energy stored in a spring compressed 0.3 m with spring constant k = 500 N/m?": "以弹簧常数K=500牛顿/米储存在弹簧压缩0.3米、弹簧常数K=500牛顿时的弹性潜在能量是多少?",
  "Elastic PE = (1/2)kx^2 = (1/2)(500)(0.3)^2 = (1/2)(500)(0.09) = 22.5 J. This equals the work done to compress the spring by 0.3 m.": "Elastic PE = 1/2)kx2 = 1/2)(500)(0.3)2 = 1/2)(500)(0.09) = 22.5 J. 这等于为压缩弹簧而做的工作 0.3 m.",
  "A force F(x) = 12 - 2x N acts on an object from x = 0 to x = 6. What is the net work done?": "F(x) = 12 - 2xN 在x = 0 = x = 6. 物体上作用的F(x) = 12 - 2x N 。",
  "W = integral from 0 to 6 of (12 - 2x) dx = [12x - x^2] from 0 to 6 = (72 - 36) - 0 = 36 J.": "W=0至6(12-2x)dx=[12x-x2];0至6=(72-36)-0=36J。",
  "What is 'work' in the physics sense as computed by integration?": "用集成计算出来的物理学意义上的“工作”是什么?",
  "In physics, work is defined as the integral of force with respect to displacement: W = integral of F(x) dx. For a constant force, this reduces to W = F * d. Work represents the energy transferred by a force.": "在物理学中,工作被定义为与流离失所有关的力量的有机组成部分:W = F(x) dx的有机组成部分。 对于恒力而言,这减少到W = F * d。 工作代表一种力量所转移的能量。",
  "What is the 'work-energy theorem'?": "\"工作能源理论\"是什么?",
  "The work-energy theorem states W_net = delta KE = (1/2)mv_f^2 - (1/2)mv_i^2. The net work done on an object by all forces equals the change in the object's kinetic energy.": "工作能量定理表示 W_net = delta KE = (1/2)mv_f2 - (1/2)mv_i2) 。 所有力量对一个对象所做的净工作等于该对象动能的变化 。",
  "What is 'gravitational potential energy'?": "什么是“重力潜在能源”?",
  "Gravitational potential energy (near Earth's surface) is the energy stored due to an object's height in a gravitational field: PE = mgh. It equals the work done against gravity to lift the object to height h from a reference level.": "引力潜在能量(接近地球表面)是指由于物体在引力场的高度而储存的能量:PE = mgh。它等于在重力下将物体从参考水平提升到h高度的工作。",
  "What is the meaning of 'foot-pound' as a unit?": "\"脚磅\"作为一个单位是什么意思?",
  "A foot-pound (ft-lb) is the British/imperial unit of work or energy. It is the amount of work done when a force of one pound moves an object a distance of one foot in the direction of the force. It is analogous to the newton-meter (joule) in SI.": "一英尺(ft-lb)是英国/帝国的工作单位或能量单位,是一磅力将物体向部队方向移动一英尺距离时完成的工作量,类似于SI的牛顿计(joule)。",
  "What is 'power' in the context of work and energy?": "在工作和能源方面,什么是“力量”?",
  "Power is the rate at which work is done: P = dW/dt. It can also be expressed as P = F*v (force times velocity). The SI unit is the watt (W), where 1 W = 1 J/s.": "P=dW/dt。也可以以P=F*v(强度速度)表示。SI单位是瓦特(W),其中1 W=1 J/s。",
  "A 500-kg wrecking ball swings down from a height of 4 m. Using conservation of energy (g = 9.8 m/s^2), what is its speed at the bottom of the swing?": "利用节能(g = 9.8 m/s2),在秋千底部的速度如何?",
  "By conservation of energy, mgh = (1/2)mv^2, so v = sqrt(2gh) = sqrt(2*9.8*4) = sqrt(78.4) = 8.85 m/s (approximately). Mass cancels, so the speed is independent of the mass of the wrecking ball.": "通过节能, mgh = (1/2)mv2, 因此 v = sqrt( 2gh) = sqrt(2*9.8*4) = sqrt( 78.4) = 8.85 m/s( 约) 。 质量取消, 因此速度与残骸球的质量无关 。",
  "An athlete throws a 0.5 kg ball. The force on the ball during the throw varies as F(x) = 100(1 - x/0.6) N for 0 <= x <= 0.6 m (the length of the throwing motion). What is the ball's speed when released?": "运动员投出0.5公斤球。投球时球的强度为 F(x) = 100(1 - x/0. 6) N, 0 = * x = = 0. 0. 6 m(投球的长度) 。投球时的速率是多少?",
  "W = integral from 0 to 0.6 of 100(1 - x/0.6) dx = 100[x - x^2/1.2] from 0 to 0.6 = 100(0.6 - 0.3) = 30 J. By the work-energy theorem, 30 = (1/2)(0.5)v^2, so v^2 = 120, v = sqrt(120) = 10.95 m/s. Checking: (1/2)(0.5)(10.95)^2 = 0.25*119.9 = 30. So v = 10.95. Looking at options again, 10.95 matches. But let me verify the integral: 100*[x - x^2/(2*0.6)] from 0 to 0.6 = 100*[0.6 - 0.36/1.2] = 100*[0.6 - 0.3] = 30 J. So v = sqrt(2*30/0.5) = sqrt(120) = 10.95 m/s.": "W=100(1 - x/0.6) dx=100[xxxxxxx2/2/1.2]x0-0.6=100(0.6-0.3)=30 J。用工作能量定理,30=1/2)(0.5)v=2,v=2=120,v=Sqrt(120)=10.95m/s。检查:(1/2)(0.5)(10.95)2=0.25*119.9=30.So v=10.95。再看看选项,10.95匹配。但让我核查一下:100*[xxxxxx/2(2*0.6)]x0.6=100*[0.6 -0.36/1.2]=100*[0.6 -0.3]=100*[0.6]=30J.V=Sqrt(2*30/0.5)=Sqrt(120)=10.95m/s。",
  "An amusement park ride uses a spring launcher (k = 8000 N/m) compressed by 2 m to launch a 400 kg car up a frictionless ramp. Using conservation of energy, what is the maximum height the car reaches (g = 9.8 m/s^2)?": "游乐场乘游艇使用弹簧发射器(k = 8000 N/m),压缩2米,将400公斤的汽车发射到无摩擦坡道上。 使用节能,车最高高度(g = 9.8 m/s=2)是多少(g = 9.8 m/s=2)?",
  "Spring PE converts to gravitational PE: (1/2)kx^2 = mgh. So h = kx^2/(2mg) = 8000(4)/(2*400*9.8) = 32000/7840 = 4.08 m (approximately).": "Spring PE 转换为引力PE:1/2)kx=2 = mgh. 所以 h = kx2/(2mg) = 8000(4)/(2*400*9.8) = 32000/7840 = 4.08米(约合)。",
  "A factory conveyor belt moves packages using a force F(x) = 20*e^(-x/5) N. How much work is done moving a package from x = 0 to x = 10 m?": "使用F(x) = 20*e(x/5)/(N)的F(x) = 20*e(x/5)的工厂传送带移动包件。 将包件从x = 0 = x = 10米移动到x = 10米完成多少工作?",
  "W = integral from 0 to 10 of 20*e^(-x/5) dx = 20[-5*e^(-x/5)] from 0 to 10 = -100[e^(-2) - e^0] = -100(e^(-2) - 1) = 100(1 - e^(-2)) J.": "W = 20 * * (-x/5) dx = 20 [-5 * e% (-x/5)] 0 = 10 = - 100 [e% (-2) - e%0] = - 100 (e% (-2) - 1) = 100(1 - e% (2) J。",
  "A garage door spring system uses two springs, each with k = 200 N/m. Together they must do 400 J of work to lift the door. How far must each spring be stretched from its natural length?": "车库门的弹簧系统使用两个弹簧,每个弹簧K=200牛顿/米。他们必须一起做400J的工作才能把门抬起来。 每一弹簧的自然长度必须伸展到多远?",
  "Each spring stores half the energy: 200 J. For one spring: 200 = (1/2)(200)x^2 = 100x^2. So x^2 = 2, giving x = sqrt(2) = 1.414 m (approximately 1.41 m).": "每个春季储存一半的能量:200焦耳。 对于一个春季:200=1/2)(200)x%2=100x%2。 So x=2=2,给x=Sqrt(2)=1.414米(约1.41米)。"
